                            <comment id="15708140" author="anoop.hbase" created="Wed, 30 Nov 2016 10:11:18 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;cc &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=carp84&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;carp84&quot;&gt;Yu Li&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=dvdreddy&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;dvdreddy&quot;&gt;deepankar&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15708168" author="apache9" created="Wed, 30 Nov 2016 10:24:47 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Is it possible to just remove the L1 on heap cache as you said that off heap L2 can perform equally with on heap L1?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15708186" author="anoop.hbase" created="Wed, 30 Nov 2016 10:34:26 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Should be a much involved change and more to test around that..  Will do some study on that.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15708801" author="carp84" created="Wed, 30 Nov 2016 14:58:29 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;+1 on turning L2 off heap cache ON.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;We&apos;re using 42GB on heap size with 12GB offheap cache here in Alibaba search. But according to our &lt;a href=&quot;http://hbase.apache.org/book.html#ops.capacity.nodes.gc&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;ref guide&lt;/a&gt; we are recommending ~20-24GB or less memory dedicated to one RS. Plus the default value of &lt;tt&gt;hfile.block.cache.size&lt;/tt&gt; set to 0.4, maybe set default size of off heap size to 8-10GB is a good idea?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15709079" author="anoop.hbase" created="Wed, 30 Nov 2016 16:49:15 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks Yu Li..  Ya same I was also thinking. Having a default value of 8GB.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15709232" author="stack" created="Wed, 30 Nov 2016 17:43:12 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;We can come out w/ new defaults for 2.0 (with refguide appropriately updated).&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;+1 on enabling by default.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;We need to do a bit of work though first.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;We need to decide on a new config., direct memory size in MB/G. The L2 is some proportion of this.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;If L2, then L1 should be shrunk.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;If L2, then heap should be smaller?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Do we need a &apos;configure&apos; that spits out basic templates for hbase-env.sh? Or a file sourced by hbase-env.sh that has in it heap, offheap, sizings set?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Then there is the L2 BucketCache itself. It needs a bit of work. &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-15240&quot; title=&quot;Go Big BucketCache Fixes&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;HBASE-15240&quot;&gt;HBASE-15240&lt;/a&gt; has some outstanding items (Let me add a few more I have from working notes kept around last time I messed w/ bucketcache).&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15712024" author="anoop.hbase" created="Thu, 1 Dec 2016 13:56:03 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Agree Stack. There are some jiras which must be fixed before doing this.  I will link whatever am coming across.. Pls link if any thing is missing.&lt;br/&gt;
There is also another issue of memory fragmentation by BC which is raised by &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=dvdreddy&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;dvdreddy&quot;&gt;deepankar&lt;/a&gt;. That is also a blocker.  &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-16630&quot; title=&quot;Fragmentation in long running Bucket Cache&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;HBASE-16630&quot;&gt;HBASE-16630&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
